📁 Where to Find the public/images Folder:

When you create a React project using tools like Vite or Create React App, the folder structure usually looks like this:

kotlin
my-project/
│
├── public/
│   └── images/      ← ✅ This is where you should put your product images
│
├── src/
│   ├── App.jsx
│   └── ...
├── package.json

🛠️ If You Don't See an images Folder

Just create it manually:

  1. Open your project folder.

  2. Go into the public/ directory.

  3. Right-click > New Folder > Name it images.

  4. Paste or save your product images (like coke.jpg, pepsi.jpg) inside.

🖼️ Referencing Images in Your Code

Once the images are inside public/images, you can reference them in your React code like this:

jsx
<img src="/images/coke.jpg" alt="Coca-Cola" />

✅ Don't include public/ in the path — React automatically serves files from there.
